{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":315,"text":"I was about 10 years old"},{"time":2572,"text":"on a camping trip with my dad"},{"time":4271,"text":"in the Adirondack Mountains, a wilderness area"},{"time":7031,"text":"in the northern part of New York State."},{"time":10026,"text":"It was a beautiful day."},{"time":11467,"text":"The forest was sparkling."},{"time":13469,"text":"The sun made the leaves glow like stained glass,"},{"time":16993,"text":"and if it weren't for the path we were following,"},{"time":20198,"text":"we could almost pretend we were"},{"time":21602,"text":"the first human beings to ever walk that land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25164,"text":"We got to our campsite."},{"time":26815,"text":"It was a lean-to on a bluff"},{"time":28782,"text":"looking over a crystal, beautiful lake,"},{"time":31478,"text":"when I discovered a horror."},{"time":34174,"text":"Behind the lean-to was a dump,"},{"time":37272,"text":"maybe 40 feet square"},{"time":38730,"text":"with rotting apple cores"},{"time":41043,"text":"and balled-up aluminum foil,"},{"time":42790,"text":"and a dead sneaker."},{"time":44539,"text":"And I was astonished,"},{"time":47110,"text":"I was very angry, and I was deeply confused."},{"time":50542,"text":"The campers who were too lazy"},{"time":52124,"text":"to take out what they had brought in,"},{"time":54082,"text":"who did they think would clean up after them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":57927,"text":"That question stayed with me,"},{"time":59836,"text":"and it simplified a little."},{"time":61803,"text":"Who cleans up after us?"},{"time":64179,"text":"However you configure"},{"time":65601,"text":"or wherever you place the us,"},{"time":67308,"text":"who cleans up after us in Istanbul?"},{"time":69898,"text":"Who cleans up after us in Rio"},{"time":72154,"text":"or in Paris or in London?"},{"time":74683,"text":"Here in New York,"},{"time":76255,"text":"the Department of Sanitation cleans up after us,"},{"time":78847,"text":"to the tune of 11,000 tons of garbage"},{"time":81517,"text":"and 2,000 tons of recyclables every day."},{"time":85879,"text":"I wanted to get to know them as individuals."},{"time":88512,"text":"I wanted to understand who takes the job."},{"time":91358,"text":"What's it like to wear the uniform"},{"time":93877,"text":"and bear that burden?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":95531,"text":"So I started a research project with them."},{"time":98184,"text":"I rode in the trucks and walked the routes"},{"time":100723,"text":"and interviewed people in offices and facilities"},{"time":103132,"text":"all over the city,"},{"time":104639,"text":"and I learned a lot,"},{"time":106378,"text":"but I was still an outsider."},{"time":108727,"text":"I needed to go deeper."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110605,"text":"So I took the job as a sanitation worker."},{"time":113721,"text":"I didn't just ride in the trucks now. I drove the trucks."},{"time":116368,"text":"And I operated the mechanical brooms and I plowed the snow."},{"time":119513,"text":"It was a remarkable privilege"},{"time":121412,"text":"and an amazing education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124019,"text":"Everyone asks about the smell."},{"time":126171,"text":"It's there, but it's not as prevalent as you think,"},{"time":129231,"text":"and on days when it is really bad,"},{"time":130745,"text":"you get used to it rather quickly."},{"time":133421,"text":"The weight takes a long time to get used to."},{"time":136618,"text":"I knew people who were several years on the job"},{"time":138905,"text":"whose bodies were still adjusting to the burden"},{"time":141490,"text":"of bearing on your body"},{"time":143571,"text":"tons of trash every week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146550,"text":"Then there's the danger."},{"time":148734,"text":"According to the Bureau of Labor Statistics,"},{"time":151206,"text":"sanitation work is one of the 10 most dangerous"},{"time":153408,"text":"occupations in the country,"},{"time":155300,"text":"and I learned why."},{"time":157051,"text":"You're in and out of traffic all day,"},{"time":158472,"text":"and it's zooming around you."},{"time":159433,"text":"It just wants to get past you, so it's often"},{"time":161317,"text":"the motorist is not paying attention."},{"time":163367,"text":"That's really bad for the worker."},{"time":165193,"text":"And then the garbage itself is full of hazards"},{"time":167353,"text":"that often fly back out of the truck"},{"time":169372,"text":"and do terrible harm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171453,"text":"I also learned about the relentlessness of trash."},{"time":174268,"text":"When you step off the curb"},{"time":175579,"text":"and you see a city from behind a truck,"},{"time":178428,"text":"you come to understand that trash"},{"time":180214,"text":"is like a force of nature unto itself."},{"time":182831,"text":"It never stops coming."},{"time":185287,"text":"It's also like a form of respiration or circulation."},{"time":188766,"text":"It must always be in motion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191811,"text":"And then there's the stigma."},{"time":193859,"text":"You put on the uniform, and you become invisible"},{"time":196775,"text":"until someone is upset with you for whatever reason"},{"time":199079,"text":"like you've blocked traffic with your truck,"},{"time":201394,"text":"or you're taking a break too close to their home,"},{"time":204045,"text":"or you're drinking coffee in their diner,"},{"time":207159,"text":"and they will come and scorn you,"},{"time":209569,"text":"and tell you that they don't want you anywhere near them."},{"time":212831,"text":"I find the stigma especially ironic,"},{"time":215263,"text":"because I strongly believe that sanitation workers"},{"time":218574,"text":"are the most important labor force"},{"time":220254,"text":"on the streets of the city, for three reasons."},{"time":223278,"text":"They are the first guardians of public health."},{"time":226060,"text":"If they're not taking away trash"},{"time":228466,"text":"efficiently and effectively every day,"},{"time":230740,"text":"it starts to spill out of its containments,"},{"time":233451,"text":"and the dangers inherent to it threaten us"},{"time":237177,"text":"in very real ways."},{"time":238351,"text":"Diseases we've had in check for decades and centuries"},{"time":241322,"text":"burst forth again and start to harm us."},{"time":244228,"text":"The economy needs them."},{"time":245900,"text":"If we can't throw out the old stuff,"},{"time":248826,"text":"we have no room for the new stuff,"},{"time":250716,"text":"so then the engines of the economy"},{"time":252785,"text":"start to sputter when consumption is compromised."},{"time":255714,"text":"I'm not advocating capitalism, I'm just pointing out their relationship."},{"time":259778,"text":"And then there's what I call"},{"time":261766,"text":"our average, necessary quotidian velocity."},{"time":265978,"text":"By that I simply mean"},{"time":267027,"text":"how fast we're used to moving"},{"time":269279,"text":"in the contemporary day and age."},{"time":271411,"text":"We usually don't care for, repair, clean, carry around"},{"time":276755,"text":"our coffee cup, our shopping bag,"},{"time":279392,"text":"our bottle of water."},{"time":280877,"text":"We use them, we throw them out, we forget about them,"},{"time":283556,"text":"because we know there's a workforce"},{"time":285336,"text":"on the other side that's going to take it all away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288356,"text":"So I want to suggest today a couple of ways"},{"time":290803,"text":"to think about sanitation that will perhaps help"},{"time":295317,"text":"ameliorate the stigma"},{"time":297791,"text":"and bring them into this conversation"},{"time":300022,"text":"of how to craft a city that is sustainable and humane."},{"time":305612,"text":"Their work, I think, is kind of liturgical."},{"time":309773,"text":"They're on the streets every day, rhythmically."},{"time":312234,"text":"They wear a uniform in many cities."},{"time":314295,"text":"You know when to expect them."},{"time":316164,"text":"And their work lets us do our work."},{"time":320087,"text":"They are almost a form of reassurance."},{"time":322878,"text":"The flow that they maintain"},{"time":324615,"text":"keeps us safe from ourselves,"},{"time":326605,"text":"from our own dross, our cast-offs,"},{"time":329242,"text":"and that flow must be maintained always"},{"time":332500,"text":"no matter what."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334133,"text":"On the day after September 11 in 2001,"},{"time":337857,"text":"I heard the growl of a sanitation truck on the street,"},{"time":341144,"text":"and I grabbed my infant son and I ran downstairs"},{"time":343456,"text":"and there was a man doing his paper recycling route"},{"time":346298,"text":"like he did every Wednesday."},{"time":348480,"text":"And I tried to thank him for doing his work"},{"time":350900,"text":"on that day of all days,"},{"time":353025,"text":"but I started to cry."},{"time":355626,"text":"And he looked at me,"},{"time":357310,"text":"and he just nodded, and he said,"},{"time":360734,"text":"\"We're going to be okay."},{"time":363612,"text":"We're going to be okay.\""},{"time":366253,"text":"It was a little while later that I started"},{"time":367606,"text":"my research with sanitation,"},{"time":368986,"text":"and I met that man again."},{"time":370400,"text":"His name is Paulie, and we worked together many times,"},{"time":373317,"text":"and we became good friends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375140,"text":"I want to believe that Paulie was right."},{"time":377967,"text":"We are going to be okay."},{"time":380169,"text":"But in our effort to reconfigure"},{"time":382146,"text":"how we as a species exist on this planet,"},{"time":385187,"text":"we must include and take account of"},{"time":388482,"text":"all the costs, including the very real human cost"},{"time":392275,"text":"of the labor."},{"time":393779,"text":"And we also would be well informed"},{"time":396580,"text":"to reach out to the people who do that work"},{"time":398798,"text":"and get their expertise"},{"time":400643,"text":"on how do we think about,"},{"time":402396,"text":"how do we create systems around sustainability"},{"time":405646,"text":"that perhaps take us from curbside recycling,"},{"time":409125,"text":"which is a remarkable success across 40 years,"},{"time":411710,"text":"across the United States and countries around the world,"},{"time":414948,"text":"and lift us up to a broader horizon"},{"time":417750,"text":"where we're looking at other forms of waste"},{"time":420636,"text":"that could be lessened"},{"time":422121,"text":"from manufacturing and industrial sources."},{"time":424854,"text":"Municipal waste, what we think of when we talk about garbage,"},{"time":428859,"text":"accounts for three percent of the nation's waste stream."},{"time":432857,"text":"It's a remarkable statistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435244,"text":"So in the flow of your days,"},{"time":437722,"text":"in the flow of your lives,"},{"time":439248,"text":"next time you see someone whose job is"},{"time":442276,"text":"to clean up after you,"},{"time":445419,"text":"take a moment to acknowledge them."},{"time":447908,"text":"Take a moment to say thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452500,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}